<h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-4">GDL (Go-Duck Language)</h1>
<p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">The standard DSL for generating your massive suite of code from a simple text file.</p>

<section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 border-b pb-2">GDL Syntax & Structure</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">GDL (Go-Duck Language) allows you to define your core business entities and the relationships between them. It looks and acts slightly similarly to JHipster's JDL.</p>

    <pre><code class="language-plaintext">@Audited 
entity Article {
  title String required unique
  content Text required
  publishedDate LocalDate
  views Integer
  metadata JSONB
}

entity Author {
  name String required
  biography Text
  settings JSON
}

relationship OneToMany {
  Author{article} to Article{author} required
}</code></pre>
</section>

<section class="mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 border-b pb-2">Supported Data Types</h2>
    <table class="min-w-full text-left bg-white border border-gray-200">
